author: ecee
text: Do you think your children (or the next generation of children) will inherit a world that is overall better than the current one or worse? In what ways will the future be better or worse?

I am not keen on how tech advances are affecting the younger generations - their communication skills, there sense of sociability. I also think that sitting by a screen is worse for physicality and introduces things into the family environment which are not healthy for young adults. I loved being outside all day and learning from nature

message_string: What did your parents teach you about love?

text: What did your parents teach you about love?
message_string: That's a tricky one. I never had my dad in my life. He up and left when he found out my mom was pregnant. My mom has a learning disability and hasn't taught me much. I think my mom and the rest of my family see love as forgiveness and just being there for each other no matter how hard things get.

message_string: How about you?

author: 0b8e
text: What did your parents teach you about love?
message_string: That must have been really hard to go through as a child.

text: What did your parents teach you about love?
message_string: I am kinda the same. My parents got divorced when I was around 5 and their relationship was just toxic. If they taught me anything about love it was to do the opposite of what they did! But when you are young you really dont know, so i dont hold that against them. So even though it wasnt good they still taught me what love was not!

text: What did your parents teach you about love?
message_string: That's a great way to think about it. It's good to know what love isn't so that you can make good choices in your future relationships. I'm sorry you had that experience. I sympathize with your situation.

author: cb71
text: What is your job or occupation? Describe a typical day.
message_string: That sounds like a pretty calm routine, and it's good that you've found a way to study and earn a bit from home. message_string: Yeah, I do. One I’ve enjoyed recently is *Black Mirror*. I like it because each episode is its own story, and it explores how technology can affect people’s lives in unexpected ways. Some episodes are unsettling, but they’re interesting because they make you think about how close some of those scenarios feel to real life.

author: b7ce
text: Do you have a favorite TV show or one you watched recently that you particularly enjoyed? Describe it.
message_string: Black Mirror is one of my favorites too. It's like a modern Twilight Zone, and I like all of the opportunities it gives to challenge the way I think about the world. I like the tensions and the thrills, and they often have nice aesthetics.
